T*
(1. Goal of the technical setup) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The purpose of this repository is not only to store code, but to define a controlled) Tj
T*
(implementation environment for the thesis experiment described in Assignment 3. The research) Tj
T*
(question asks whether demographic structure improves the explanation of variation in) Tj
T*
(hospital service use across GP practices in Scotland when compared with a simpler baseline) Tj
T*
(based on practice size and GP availability. Assignment 4 therefore focuses on the) Tj
T*
(engineering side of the thesis: the repository must be understandable to a third party,) Tj
T*
(executable from documented commands, and structured in a way that makes future experiments) Tj
T*
(traceable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The design target was practical reproducibility. A supervisor or reviewer should be able to) Tj
T*
(identify where raw inputs are placed, how they are transformed, which configuration produced) Tj
T*
(a given result, and where the resulting metrics and model artifacts were written. This means) Tj
T*
(that the repository must expose a clear pipeline, deterministic execution rules, and) Tj
T*
(structured output storage.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Repository architecture and separation of concerns) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository now follows a conventional data-science engineering layout:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- data/raw/ contains immutable source files,) Tj
T*
(- data/processed/ contains derived analytical tables generated by scripts,) Tj
T*
(- src/ contains reusable Python modules and thin command wrappers,) Tj
T*
(- config/ contains the global configuration and per-experiment overrides,) Tj
T*
(- reports/ contains run-specific metrics and metadata,) Tj
T*
(- models/ contains serialized model artifacts,) Tj
T*
(- docs/ contains the reproducibility protocol and this technical description.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This separation is important because notebook-only or script-only workflows often hide) Tj
T*
(intermediate steps. In the current structure, preprocessing logic is isolated in) Tj
T*
(src/data_pipeline.py, model construction and evaluation live in src/modeling.py, experiment) Tj
T*
(artifact management is centralized in src/tracking.py, and the command modules) Tj
T*
(\(preprocess.py, train.py, evaluate.py\) serve as clean entry points rather than places where) Tj
T*
(all logic is mixed together.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository also exposes a single execution pattern through python -m src <command>) Tj
T*
(--config .... This unifies how the project is run and removes ambiguity about which script) Tj
T*
(should be called.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Data flow and preprocessing decisions) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current reproducibility scaffold uses the raw workbook) Tj
T*
(gp_practice_population_demographics_merged.xlsx stored locally in data/raw/. During) Tj
T*
(preprocessing, the pipeline reads the data worksheet, validates the required columns, parses) Tj
T*
(dates, and converts the long-format demographic table into a one-row-per-practice-and-date) Tj
T*
(analytical table. The Sex == "All" rows provide total population and age-band counts, while) Tj
T*
(the Sex == "Female" rows are merged back in to derive a female population share.) Tj
ET
