(4. Configuration management and experiment design) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Configuration is split into one shared file and two experiment overrides. config/base.yaml) Tj
T*
(defines the project-level settings: paths, Python version, seed, preprocessing defaults,) Tj
T*
(output locations, and tracking conventions. The files experiment_f0.yaml and) Tj
T*
(experiment_f1.yaml extend this base configuration and specify only the experimental) Tj
T*
(differences that matter for comparison.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This design is deliberate. Assignment 4 explicitly requires that experiments are not run by) Tj
T*
(manual editing inside scripts. By placing the feature sets and model parameters in YAML, the) Tj
T*
(repository makes the difference between experiments inspectable and versionable. The) Tj
T*
(baseline experiment F0 uses AllAges and gp_availability, while the extended experiment F1) Tj
T*
(adds share_age_65_plus, share_female, deprivation_index, and categorical regional controls) Tj
T*
(\(HB, HSCP\). The scripts never need to be edited to move from one experiment to the other;) Tj
T*
(only the configuration changes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The configuration system also supports traceability. Each training run writes out a frozen) Tj
T*
(config_snapshot.yaml into the corresponding report folder. This means the exact merged) Tj
T*
(configuration used for the run is stored next to the results, even if the human-readable) Tj
T*
(source file changes later.) Tj
T*
() Tj
