() Tj
T*
(6. Reproducibility and traceability mechanisms) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Several concrete engineering decisions were introduced to satisfy reproducibility) Tj
T*
(requirements.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(First, dependency versions are pinned in both requirements.txt and environment.yml, and the) Tj
T*
(Python version is specified as 3.11.9. This avoids ambiguity caused by newer interpreters or) Tj
T*
(incompatible wheels. Second, seed handling is centralized in the configuration, and the) Tj
T*
(runtime explicitly fixes Python and NumPy randomness before training. Third, all paths are) Tj
T*
(resolved relative to the project root so there are no hard-coded absolute machine-specific) Tj
T*
(paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The most important traceability mechanism is the deterministic run slug. Each run folder) Tj
T*
(under reports/runs/ is named from the experiment name, configuration hash, and seed. This) Tj
T*
(gives a stable mapping from configuration to artifact location. The folder contains:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- metrics.json,) Tj
T*
(- metadata.json,) Tj
T*
(- config_snapshot.yaml.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In parallel, models/<run_slug>/model.joblib stores the serialized estimator, and) Tj
T*
(reports/experiment_registry.json stores the global mapping between configuration, run slug,) Tj
T*
(metrics path, model path, and summary metrics. The metadata file also records the processed) Tj
T*
(dataset hash and git commit hash, which is essential for linking thesis results back to the) Tj
T*
(exact code state that generated them.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. Why this design matches the academic requirement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(From an academic perspective, the repository now supports software-engineering discipline) Tj
T*
(without pretending to be production infrastructure. The design is intentionally simple, but) Tj
T*
(it enforces the core properties that matter in an engineering thesis:) Tj
ET
